title: node: Type spawn's args as a ReadonlyArray of string
body:
At the moment, this snippet:

```ts
const spawnArgs: ReadonlyArray<string> = ['foo', 'bar'];
spawn('foobar', spawnArgs);
```

fails with:

```
Argument of type 'ReadonlyArray<string>' is not assignable to parameter of type 'string[] | undefined'.
  Type 'ReadonlyArray<string>' is not assignable to type 'string[]'.
```

Looking at https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/master/lib/child_process.js#L514-L535 and https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/master/lib/internal/child_process.js#L286, it _looks_ like there is no mutation of the array. I am no expert so I'd be happy to be proven wrong, I just couldn't find sufficient evidence that a `ReadonlyArray` wouldn't be fine.
This is not a breaking change because passing a `string[]` is still valid.

body:
This is basically to cleanup the sinon types and sort out the recent 5.x release. A few things have been removed, a few have been tightened or simplified.

- [x] Static members have all been merged into one declaration for readability

- [x] `fakeTimer.runToFrame()` added
- [x] `fakeTimer.uninstall()` added (`restore` was/is an alias of this all along)
- [x] `FakeXMLHttpRequest` cleaned up, some statics were incorrectly on the prototype instead
- [x] all-optional interfaces replaced with `Partial<T>`
- [x] `hasNested`, `every` and `some` matchers added
- [x] sandbox config types tightened
- [x] `sinon.fake` added (see [here](http://sinonjs.org/releases/v5.0.3/fakes/))
- [x] `sandbox.replace` added
- [x] `sandbox.replaceGetter` added
- [x] `sandbox.replaceSetter` added
- [x] **sinon static/namespace now inherits sandbox**
- [x] legacy sandbox interface added
- [x] sinon namespace types cleaned up and tightened
- [x] conditional types (TypeScript 2.8) used for stubbed instances (#25656)

This PR aims to allow the non-null assertion operator to be used on return values from various ProseMirror APIs. Prior to TypeScript 2.8, the non-null assertion operator could be used to remove `void` from a union type (see https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/23847#issuecomment-386194536), but this behaviour was actually a bug.

So basically this PR makes ProseMirror types compatible with 2.8 where the non-null assertion operator is used.

I was writing definitions for [gulp-svgmin](https://www.npmjs.com/package/gulp-svgmin) and found myself needing to reuse `svgo`s `Options` type, but only the class is exported. I created a namespace declaration and moved the `Options` type into it. Im not sure whether this was the right approach, and whether, having created the namespace, I should also move all the other declarations into it; I decided to be conservative. Any guidance would be appreciated.
